"&#xa0;\nWritten evidence from \nLiam Good\n (CYS0078)\nI urge the committee to conduct a full economic assessment of the costs to society of motorised transport.  These costs should include measure of:\n-\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \ncosts\n of road maintenance, with consideration to the fact that damage to roads increases exponentially with vehicle weight (basic physics).\n-\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \ncosts of lung diseases caused by pollution\n-\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \ncosts of obesity and diabetes (among other diseases) which are in large part c\naused by immobility\n-\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \ncost\ns\n of dedicating massive areas of cities to road surfaces and parking. This would include for example damage caused by flooding due to poor water absorption in areas that are heavily sealed\n-\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \ncosts of environmental damage\n-\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \ncosts of clea\nning up after cars\n-\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \ncosts of having to sound proof buildings near roads\n-\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \ncosts of pollution damage to public and private buildings\n-\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \ncosts of licencing, policing, administration and accounting associated with motorised transport\nThis is a partial list, but a\n t\nally of such costs \nwill help:\n-\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nthe committee to begin to appreciate that any costs absorbed through infrastructure investment in cycling are miniscule in comparison to the massive costs absorbed to maintain motorised transport.\n-\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nto counter the idiotic statem\nents made by motorists who suggest that the road tax they pay covers the costs of damage\n-\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nus to begin to understand that motorised vehicles cost society heavily in many different ways\nFinally, the committee should appreciate that\n,\n with the majority of voter\ns being motorists, politicians will find it \ndifficult to do the right thing with regard to transport policy. \n \nThere will always be costs associated with the need for transport.   We should understand these costs and then appreciate that progress can be ma\nde with cycling, which incurs far fewer costs and even provides health benefit.\nIt is a no-\nbrainer, but there are a lot of\n low-brainers out there \nwho\n have been stopping progress away\n from our bike unfriendly infrastructure.\n&#xa0;\nDecember 2013\n&#xa0;\n"